body:
Can u tell me how i can remove transparency from the image in PNG format in .NET Core 2.0?
I do something like this, but as a result, the picture is obtained with serrated edges and doesn't look beautiful + this operation takes a very long time
```
var original = SKBitmap.Decode(inputStream);
if (original.ColorType == SKColorType.Index8)
{
    original.CopyTo(original, SKImageInfo.PlatformColorType);
}

for (int i = 0; i < original.Width; i++)
{
    for (int j = 0; j < original.Height; j++)
    {
        if (original.GetPixel(i, j) == SKColors.Empty)
        {
            original.SetPixel(i, j, SKColors.White);
        }
    }
}
```
Can u help me?
Thanks in advance for the answer.
